HEADWORD: Lyrated
<hw>Ly"ra*ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[NL. <ets>lyratus</ets>. See
<er>Lyre</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Lyre-shaped, or
spatulate and oblong, with small lobes toward the base; <as>as, a
<ex>lyrate</ex> leaf</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Shaped like a lyre, as the tail
of the blackcock, or that of the lyre bird.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lyre</ent>⟦br⟧
